Ex-Watford striker, Troy Deeney, has claimed that Mauricio Pochettino and Harry Kane will join Manchester United this summer. Deeney also tipped Paul Pogba to quit Old Trafford for Paris Saint-Germain. United are set to appoint a permanent manager at the end of the season, with Ralf Rangnick taking charge of the team on a temporary basis following Ole Gunnar Solskjaer’s sacking in November. Pochettino, who is currently at Paris Saint-Germain, is one of the frontrunners to take over at the Theatre of Dreams. Deeney, who now plays for Birmingham City, also Kane to leave Tottenham Hotspur and join Pochettino at Manchester United. “For what it’s worth, here’s what I think will happen: Mauricio Pochettino will leave Paris Saint-Germain and go to Manchester United, as will Harry Kane. “Zinedine Zidane will go to PSG, along with Paul Pogba. Kylian Mbappe will go to Real Madrid,” Deeney wrote in a column for The Sun.